    <datafield tag="520" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
      <subfield code="a">Collection of treatises, copied in the same hand, on mathematical sciences. Topics include calculating heights, distances, areas, solving geometrical and algebraic problems, music theory. At the back of the work are three additions: 1) pages of notes, probably by the copyist, about some of the works in the collection (f. 129r-137v), 2) an added commentary on Apollonius' Conics copied in a different hand (f. 139v-143r), 3) further notes. One folio in Persian (f. 71) is misplaced and should follow folio 78.</subfield>
    </datafield>
    <datafield tag="546" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
      <subfield code="a">Arabic with one work in Persian (number 8).</subfield>
    </datafield>
    <datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
      <subfield code="a">Title from added title (f. 1r).</subfield>
    </datafield>
    <datafield tag="505" ind1="0" ind2=" ">
      <subfield code="a">1. f. 1v-14r: Kitāb [Manālāwus] fī al-kurīyāt -- 2. f. 15v-18v: ʻAn murabbaʻ mutasāwī al-aḍlāʻ / Muẓaffar ibn Muḥammad al-Ṭūsī -- 3. f. 18v-24r: Maqālah fī istikhrāj irtifāʻ al-quṭb / al-Ḥasan ibn al-Ḥusayn ibn al-Haytham -- 4. f. 24r-25r: Ashkāl nāfiʻah fī kitāb Arshimīdas -- 5. f. 25r-30v: Fī masāḥat al-dāʼirah / Arshimīdas -- 6. f. 30v-48v: Kitāb Arisṭākhus fī jirmay al-nayyirayn wa-abʻādihimā / Arisṭākhus -- 7. f. 49r-75v: Kitāb al-lāmiʻ fī amthāl al-Zīj al-jāmiʻ / ʻAlī ibn Aḥmad al-Nasawī -- 8. f. 76v-81r: Risālat al-tazyīn fī ḥisāb jadwal al-thalāthīn [in Persian] -- 9. f. 81v-109r: Maqālah fī al-jabr wa-al-muqābalah / Abū al-Fatḥ ʻUmar ibn Ibrāhīm al-Khayyāmī -- 10. 109v-111r:  Īḍāḥ al-burhān ʻalá ḥisāb al-khaṭaʼayn / Abī Saʻd Jābir ibn Ibrāhīm al-Ṣābiʼ -- 11. f. 111v-113r: Ḥāshiyah ʻalá Īḍāḥ al-burhān ʻalá ḥisāb al-khaṭaʼayn / Abū Saʻd al-Ṣābiʼ -- 12. f. 113r-115r: Muqaddimah li-ṣināʻat ālah tuʻrafu bi-hā al-abʻād / Aḥmad ibn Ibrāhīm al-Sanjarī -- 14. f. 115v-121v: Fī amr al-khaṭṭayn / Aḥmad ibn Muḥammad ibn ʻAbd al-Jalīl al-Sijzī -- 15. f. 121v-122r: Fī maʻrifat irtifāʻ al-ashkhāṣ al-qāʼimah / Abū ʻAlī ibn al-Haytham -- 16. f. 122v-125r: Masʼalah dhakarahā Abū Naṣr al-Fārābī fī al-maqālah al-ūlá min al-fann al-awwal fī al-mūsīqá / Abū Naṣr al-Fārābī -- 17. f. 125r-128v: Min kalām Abī al-Futūḥ ibn al-Surá -- 18. f. 129r-137v: [Notes] -- 19. f. 139v-143r:  [Commentary on Apollonius' Conics] -- 20. f. 144r-146v: [Notes]</subfield>
    </datafield>
    <datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
      <subfield code="a">Layout: Chiefly 19 lines per page; some marginalia.</subfield>
    </datafield>
    <datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
      <subfield code="a">Script: Written in naskh in brown ink; partially pointed.</subfield>
    </datafield>
    <datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
      <subfield code="a">Decoration: Rubrications in red; numerous geometrical diagrams in red and brown.</subfield>
    </datafield>
    <datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
      <subfield code="a">Origin: The item is not dated, but was likely produced in the 13th or 14th century based on the paper and writing. A section that was probably copied later is signed Taqī al-Dīn Naṣr al-Ḥanafī (f. 143r).</subfield>
    </datafield>
